    "_id": "b74ed15522338794",
    "name": "Net Gun",
    "type": "weapon",
    "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/equipment.webp",
    "effects": [],
    "folder": null,
    "sort": 0,
    "flags": {},
    "system": {
      "description": {
        "value": "<p>The net gun is powered by black powder charges to launch a folded net with weighted ends at an enemy to entangle them. The net is attached to two lead ropes that anchor back to the firearm. Once a net is fired, you can quickly grab these lead ropes with one hand and use them to keep the target grappled. Packing and loading the net is a difficult and time-consuming task, so net guns are often only fired once in a given engagement, though it is said that some people have mastered the art of reloading them quickly. Ammunition for a net gun is a pre-packed net charge that costs 1gp each. However, you may recover any spent charges as a 10 minute activity to repair and repack the nets.</p>"
      },
      "source": {
        "value": "Everything Archetypes: Wilderness"
      },
